<refsect2>
<title><anchor id="xmlSecBufferCreate">xmlSecBufferCreate ()</title>
<programlisting><link linkend="xmlSecBufferPtr">xmlSecBufferPtr</link> xmlSecBufferCreate          (<link linkend="size-t">size_t</link> size);</programlisting>
<para>
Allocates and initalizes new memory buffer with given size.
Caller is responsible for calling <link linkend="xmlSecBufferDestroy">xmlSecBufferDestroy</link> function
to free the buffer.</para>
<para>

</para><informaltable pgwide="1" frame="none" role="params">
<tgroup cols="2">
<colspec colwidth="2*">
<colspec colwidth="8*">
<tbody>
<row><entry align="right"><parameter>size</parameter>&nbsp;:</entry>
<entry> 		the intial size.
</entry></row>
<row><entry align="right"><emphasis>Returns</emphasis> :</entry><entry>pointer to newly allocated buffer or NULL if an error occurs.
</entry></row>
</tbody></tgroup></informaltable></refsect2>
